I find out that it caused by different axis-order between v1.9.0 and v1.10.0+.In file "tensorflow/contrib/lite/kernels/transpose_conv.cc",line 81,it is TF_LITE_ENSURE_EQ(context,SizeOfDimension(input, 3),SizeOfDimension(weights, 0));,but in v1.10.0 and above,it is TF_LITE_ENSURE_EQ(context, SizeOfDimension(input, 3),SizeOfDimension(weights, 3));.
So,you cannot use the diffrent version when you convert the model from tensorflow to lite.

body:
I find out that it caused by different axis-order between v1.9.0 and v1.10.0+.In file "tensorflow/contrib/lite/kernels/transpose_conv.cc",line 81,it is `TF_LITE_ENSURE_EQ(context,SizeOfDimension(input, 3),SizeOfDimension(weights, 0));`,but in v1.10.0 and above,it is `TF_LITE_ENSURE_EQ(context, SizeOfDimension(input, 3),SizeOfDimension(weights, 3));`.
So,you cannot use the diffrent version when you convert the model from tensorflow to lite.
